#### 2. Version Comparison Logic (Already Implemented)
Used in `IsNewVersionAvailable()` to compare two parsed versions.

```cpp
bool Ota::IsNewVersionAvailable(const std::string &currentVersion, const std::string &newVersion)
{
    std::vector<int> current = ParseVersion(currentVersion);
    std::vector<int> newer = ParseVersion(newVersion);

    for (size_t i = 0; i < std::min(current.size(), newer.size()); ++i)
    {
        if (newer[i] > current[i])
        {
            return true;
        }
        else if (newer[i] < current[i])
        {
            return false;
        }
    }

    return newer.size() > current.size();
}
```

This logic assumes that version numbers are dot-separated integers and handles cases where one version has more segments than another (e.g., `"1.0.1"` vs `"1.0"`). This comparison technique is widely applicable across firmware/software update systems.

